{"doc":{"isMarkdown":true,"isTranslated":true,"isActive":true,"flaws":{},"title":"ARIA 사용하기: 규칙, 상태, 속성","mdn_url":"/ko/docs/Web/Accessibility/ARIA/ARIA_Techniques","locale":"ko","native":"한국어","sidebarHTML":"","body":[{"type":"prose","value":{"id":null,"title":null,"isH3":false,"content":"<p>ARIA defines semantics that can be applied to elements, with these divided into <strong>roles</strong> (defining a type of user interface element) and <strong>states</strong> and <strong>properties</strong> that are supported by a role. Authors must assign an ARIA role and the appropriate states and properties to an element during its life-cycle, unless the element already has appropriate ARIA semantics (via use of an appropriate HTML element). Addition of ARIA semantics only exposes extra information to a browser's accessibility API, and does not affect a page's DOM.</p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"roles","title":"Roles","isH3":false,"content":""}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"widget_roles","title":"Widget roles","isH3":true,"content":"<ul>\n  <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/Accessibility/ARIA/Roles/button_role\"><code>button</code></a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/Accessibility/ARIA/Roles/checkbox_role\"><code>checkbox</code></a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/Accessibility/ARIA/Roles/gridcell_role\"><code>gridcell</code></a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/Accessibility/ARIA/Roles/link_role\"><code>link</code></a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/Accessibility/ARIA/Roles/menuitem_role\"><code>menuitem</code></a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/Accessibility/ARIA/Roles/menuitemcheckbox_role\"><code>menuitemcheckbox</code></a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/Accessibility/ARIA/Roles/menuitemradio_role\"><code>menuitemradio</code></a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/Accessibility/ARIA/Roles/option_role\"><code>option</code></a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/Accessibility/ARIA/Roles/progressbar_role\"><code>progressbar</